{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "I'm writing a MachineConfig that references a configuration file hosted on our internal HTTP server. Instead of embedding the file contents inline, I'd like to use an Ignition remote source with an HTTP URL so that each node fetches the latest version of the config file dynamically at boot or when the config is applied. Here's the snippet:\n\nstorage:\n  files:\n  - path: /etc/myapp/config.yaml\n    contents:\n      source: http://internal-server.example.com/configs/myapp.yaml\n\nCan you help me finalize this MachineConfig?"}, "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:31:07.052Z"}
