{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01RniAYXBNXfir7VU63pUcKE", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_01HHsxMEUjVsr4qRvZG9dQKj", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "grep -n \"http\\|source\\|remote\\|ignition\\|file\" /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/FAQ.md 2>/dev/null | head -30", "description": "Check FAQ documentation for HTTP/remote source references"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1506, "cache_read_input_tokens": 71494, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1506, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 24}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": "toolu_vrtx_01AmMi3GeEKAgb2HPrnNGvun", "session_id": "97616e95-6991-412d-aaaf-43b45e95d486", "uuid": "ddb989ce-32ce-4db4-989b-b82f9f71ec8b", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcK1qBqEiE9tgT4uH8ke5", "subagent_type": "Explore", "task_description": "Find MachineConfig examples with remote file sources", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:33:40.781Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01HHsxMEUjVsr4qRvZG9dQKj","type":"tool_result","content":"3:The goal of this file is to have a place to easily commit answers to questions\n33:The [Machine API Operator](https://github.com/openshift/machine-api-operator) manages \"machine\" objects which represent underlying IaaS virtual ([or physical](https://github.com/openshift-metal3)) machines.\n45:If for example you write a daemonset that writes a custom systemd unit into e.g. `/etc/systemd/system`, or do so manually via `ssh`/`oc debug node` - OS upgrades will preserve that change (via libostree), and the MCO will not revert it.  The MCO/MCD only changes files included in `MachineConfigs`, there is no code to look for \"unknown\" files.\n49:Stated more generally, on an OSTree managed system, all content in `/etc` and `/var` is [preserved by default across upgrades](https://ostreedev.github.io/ostree/adapting-existing/).\n53:If a file that *is* managed by MachineConfig is changed, the MCD will detect this and go degraded.  We go degraded rather than overwrite in order to avoid [reboot loops](https://github.com/openshift/machine-config-operator/pull/245).\n55:In the future, we would like to harden things more so that these things are more controlled, and ideally avoid having any persistent \"unmanaged\" state.  But it will take significant work to get there; and the status quo means that we can support other operators such as SDN (and e.g. [nmstate](https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate)) that may control parts of the host without the MCO's awareness.\n59:In clusters that are managed by the [Machine API](https://github.com/openshift/machine-api-operator/), see\n60:[this question](https://github.com/openshift/machine-api-operator/blob/master/FAQ.md#i-created-a-machine-but-it-never-joined-the-cluster)\n66:[this issue](https://github.com/coreos/ignition/issues/585).\n91: - https://github.com/openshift/machine-config-operator/issues/1619\n92: - https://github.com/openshift/machine-config-operator/pull/2035\n107:Or, adding the RHEL UBI repository or [full RHEL entitlements](https://docs.openshift.com/container-platform/4.13/support/remote_health_monitoring/insights-operator-simple-access.html#insights-operator-simple-access) may work.\n112:to instead switch to an [image layering](https://docs.openshift.com/container-platform/4.13/post_installation_configuration/coreos-layering.html) model.\n116:Yes, RHEL worker nodes will have a instance of the Machine Config Daemon running on them.  However, only a subset of MCO functionality is supported on RHEL worker nodes.  It is possible to create a Machine Config to write files and `systemd` units to RHEL worker nodes, but it is not possible to manage OS updates, kernel arguments, or extensions on RHEL worker nodes.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01AmMi3GeEKAgb2HPrnNGvun","session_id":"97616e95-6991-412d-aaaf-43b45e95d486","uuid":"c4cb02f0-ee2f-414b-85a8-d183a526773d","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:33:40.791Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Find MachineConfig examples with remote file sources"}
