{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01EkKCcQwP5WF9nvAWVTT9cU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# once-from\n2\t\n3\tThe promise of the next-generation OpenShift installer and Red Hat CoreOS\n4\tcombined with the machine-config-operator is fully automated management\n5\tof the hosts in a highly integrated fashion.\n6\t\n7\tHowever, we also aim to support a \"bring your own host\" model. We want to avoid\n8\tduplication as much as possible between these two code paths. The idea of the\n9\t\"once-from\" mode for the machine-config-daemon is that one can pass it an\n10\tIgnition config (as generated by the installer for example) and execute it\n11\ton a host that was already created. (The feature also supports MachineConfig\n12\tmanifests which are meant to be used for host updates rather than installation).\n13\t\n14\tThis is mostly about laying down files and systemd units and the like; we\n15\tdon't expect \"once-from\" to e.g. create users.\n16\t\n17\t# Testing once-from mode\n18\t\n19\tOnce-from should generally be used on a machine not connected to a cluster.  You can use for example a traditional CentOS 7 machine;\n20\tthis could be anything from a cloud instance to a Vagrant Box or even\n21\ta physical install.\n22\t\n23\tThis guide was written using Vagrant to make a CentOS 7 box: https://app.vagrantup.com/centos/boxes/7\n24\t\n25\tAn easy way to test this is to copy over the machine-config-daemon\n26\tbinary from `_output/linux/amd64/machine-config-daemon` to the\n27\ttarget.  (With Vagrant for example, copy to the target dir then `vagrant rsync`, the output will be in `/vagrant`).\n28\t\n29\tTo run:\n30\t\n31\t`./machine-config-daemon start --node-name $(hostname) --root-mount / --once-from $(pwd)/example.ign`\n32\t\n33\tWhere `example.ign` here is the content from https://github.com/coreos/ignition/blob/master/doc/examples.md#start-services\n34\t\n35\t```json\n36\t{\n37\t  \"ignition\": { \"version\": \"2.2.0\" },\n38\t  \"systemd\": {\n39\t    \"units\": [{\n40\t      \"name\": \"example.service\",\n41\t      \"enabled\": true,\n42\t      \"contents\": \"[Service]\\nType=oneshot\\nExecStart=/usr/bin/echo Hello World\\n\\n[Install]\\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\"\n43\t    }]\n44\t  }\n45\t}\n46\t```\n47\t\n48\tYou can also try out the MachineConfig support of \"once-from\" mode by passing a MC manifest instead, see [HACKING.md](./HACKING.md) for a MachineConfig example.\n49\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01AmMi3GeEKAgb2HPrnNGvun","session_id":"97616e95-6991-412d-aaaf-43b45e95d486","uuid":"574b3156-47c2-411b-b3be-8d5b01d70bb6","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:33:44.158Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Find MachineConfig examples with remote file sources"}
