{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01LmZYUHnbQY5pexzu4k6NPZ","type":"tool_result","content":"/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfigController.md:97:The TemplateController uses `internal templates` and a `configuration object` to generate OpenShift-owned MachineConfig objects for pre-defined `roles` like master, worker etc. These templates are stored in the `templates/` directory of this repository. For example, the `templates/master/00-master` directory will yield a MachineConfig object named `00-master` for the `master` role. Template variables such as `{{.EtcdCAData}}` are filled in using the controllerconfig custom resource (e.g. `controllerconfig/machine-config-controller`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01AmMi3GeEKAgb2HPrnNGvun","session_id":"97616e95-6991-412d-aaaf-43b45e95d486","uuid":"112f4946-807c-4e49-8486-f17468b5462f","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:33:55.501Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Find MachineConfig examples with remote file sources"}
