 with the output of the command above.\n\n## Why \"Dynamic at Boot\" Doesn't Work Here\n\nMCO's rendering pipeline (`pkg/controller/render/render.go`) intentionally flattens all MachineConfigs into a single rendered config before distribution. Every node gets the **same static snapshot**. If you need nodes to pick up config changes dynamically, the correct workflow is:\n\n1. Update the content in your MachineConfig's `data:` source\n2. Apply the updated MachineConfig to the cluster\n3. MCO rolls out the update node-by-node via its standard drain/apply/reboot cycle\n\nThis is by design \u2014 it gives MCO the ability to track, diff, and safely roll out configuration changes across the cluster.", "stop_reason": "end_turn", "session_id": "97616e95-6991-412d-aaaf-43b45e95d486", "total_cost_usd": 1.23743655, "usage": {"input_tokens": 6, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 5407, "cache_read_input_tokens": 65000, "output_tokens": 1534, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 5407}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}, "modelUsage": {"claude-sonnet-4-6": {"inputTokens": 535, "outputTokens": 14006, "cacheReadInputTokens": 2261951, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 92575, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 1.23743655, "contextWindow": 200000, "maxOutputTokens": 32000}}, "permission_denials": [{"tool_name": "Bash", "tool_use_id": "toolu_vrtx_01Vyro2nPgXk7eV1MKbCQXYx", "tool_input": {"command": "cat /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/eval/cases/case-014/input.yaml 2>/dev/null", "description": "Read the eval case-014 input YAML"}}, {"tool_name": "Bash", "tool_use_id": "toolu_vrtx_014xPAZFk99S3dqDmgozEMCy", "tool_input": {"command": "# Check all Ignition versions in vendor for URL scheme validation\nfor ver in v3_1 v3_2 v3_3 v3_5; do\n  f=\"/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-op